01:13:30,172 --> 01:13:33,938
<i>after a horrific accident involving
world champion Niki Lauda.</i>

952
01:13:34,012 --> 01:13:35,935
<i>Due to safety concerns before the race,</i>

953
01:13:36,012 --> 01:13:38,379
<i>the Austrian had said
he would not take part,</i>

954
01:13:38,412 --> 01:13:39,902
<i>but in the end he did.</i>

955
01:13:41,292 --> 01:13:43,579
<i>He was making up for lost time
when he went off the track,</i>

956
01:13:43,692 --> 01:13:46,059
<i>puncturing the Ferrari's fuel tank.</i>

957
01:13:46,452 --> 01:13:48,739
<i>Brett Lunger was unable to
avoid the flaming wreck,</i>

958
01:13:48,892 --> 01:13:51,816
<i>but was unhurt and joined with
the other drivers to rescue Lauda,</i>

959
01:13:51,892 --> 01:13:54,782
<i>who was taken to Mannheim Hospital
with severe burns,</i>

960
01:13:54,892 --> 01:13:58,533
<i>the incident reminding us again
of the dangers of Formula 1.</i>

961
01:13:58,652 --> 01:14:00,654
<i>Niki Lauda was trapped
for almost a minute</i>

962
01:14:00,732 --> 01:14:03,383
<i>in a searing inferno
of 800-plus degrees.</i>

963
01:14:12,212 --> 01:14:14,419
- Do we have any change this morning?
- No...

964
01:14:14,492 --> 01:14:16,415
Frau Lauda. Frau Lauda?

965
01:18:50,172 --> 01:18:52,061
- Morning, chaps.
- Hey, here's the man.

966
01:18:52,252 --> 01:18:53,902
Looking good.

967
01:18:57,132 --> 01:18:59,942
- What's going on?
- Jesus. It's Niki.

968
01:19:00,012 --> 01:19:02,060
- What about him?
- He's here.

969
01:19:02,372 --> 01:19:03,897
- What?
- He's racing.

970
01:19:19,252 --> 01:19:20,902
Niki.

971
01:19:27,532 --> 01:19:29,057
It's that bad, huh?

972
01:19:30,372 --> 01:19:31,783
No.

973
01:19:32,652 --> 01:19:35,576
In hospital I asked them straight,
no bullshit,

974
01:19:35,652 --> 01:19:37,495
how bad my appearance would be.

975
01:19:38,732 --> 01:19:41,099
They said with time it would be fine.

976
01:19:41,972 --> 01:19:43,576
But it won't.

977
01:19:44,492 --> 01:19:47,336
I can tell, seeing your reaction.

978
01:19:48,292 --> 01:19:51,296
I will spend the rest of my life
with a face that frightens people.

979
01:19:55,412 --> 01:19:59,178
You know, Niki, I tried to write you
a letter at the time, to apologise.

980
01:20:00,812 --> 01:20:03,292
The drivers' meeting in Germany,
before the race.

981
01:20:03,412 --> 01:20:05,938
- I swayed the room.
- Yes, you did.

982
01:20:06,132 --> 01:20:08,339
That race should never have gone ahead.

983
01:20:09,092 --> 01:20:10,696
No, it shouldn't.

984
01:20:11,132 --> 01:20:14,773
So, in many ways, I feel responsible
for what happened, and...

985
01:20:14,852 --> 01:20:16,422
You were.

986
01:20:18,092 --> 01:20:19,821
But, trust me...

987
01:20:20,972 --> 01:20:25,022
watching you win those races
while I was fighting for my life...

988
01:20:27,332 --> 01:20:30,541
...you were equally responsible
for getting me back in the car.

989
01:20:58,292 --> 01:21:00,977
- How are you feeling, Niki?
- Fine.

990
01:21:01,372 --> 01:21:04,979
Niki, can you confirm to us exactly
which procedures you've had

991
01:21:05,012 --> 01:21:07,014
and the expectations for your recovery?

992
01:21:07,572 --> 01:21:09,017
Sure.

993
01:21:09,172 --> 01:21:10,981
I had a skin graft operation,

994
01:21:11,012 --> 01:21:13,333
where they put half my right thigh
in my face.

995
01:21:15,532 --> 01:21:20,333
Now, it doesn't look too good,
but one unexpected advantage is

996
01:21:20,372 --> 01:21:22,659
it's impossible to perspire
through a skin graft,

997
01:21:22,732 --> 01:21:26,100
so sweat will never run into my eyes
again, which is good for a driver.

998
01:21:28,372 --> 01:21:30,022
When they heard about your condition,

999
01:21:30,052 --> 01:21:33,499
Ferrari immediately hired
a replacement driver, Carlos Reutemann.

1000
01:21:34,172 --> 01:21:38,177
Yeah, before even reaching the hospital.

1001
01:21:38,212 --> 01:21:40,260
Is Reutemann driving today, too?

1002
01:21:40,692 --> 01:21:43,696
Yes, and keen to make an impression.

1003
01:21:43,892 --> 01:21:47,863
So, let's see where Mr Reutemann
finishes and where I finish today.

1004
01:21:49,412 --> 01:21:52,097
James Hunt and McLaren have
caught up a lot while you were away.

1005
01:21:52,732 --> 01:21:54,222
Yes.

1006
01:21:54,852 --> 01:21:57,776
So is there a question now,
or are you just trying to piss me off?

1007
01:22:01,132 --> 01:22:02,861
You still think you can win?

1008
01:22:03,292 --> 01:22:05,056
Yes, of course.

1009
01:22:05,092 --> 01:22:07,094
I have the better car.

1010
01:22:07,212 --> 01:22:09,692
And possibly I'm the better driver.

1011
01:22:09,892 --> 01:22:12,293
But he's a clever guy,
and he's used his time well

1012
01:22:12,372 --> 01:22:16,422
while I was lying half-dead in hospital
to win some points.

1013
01:22:18,372 --> 01:22:21,057
And what did your wife say
when she saw your face?

1014
01:22:27,252 --> 01:22:30,734
She said, "Sweetie,
you don't need a face to drive.

1015
01:22:30,812 --> 01:22:32,940
"You just need a right foot."

1016
01:22:33,252 --> 01:22:35,619
I'm being serious.

1017
01:22:35,812 --> 01:22:40,295
Do you really think your marriage can
survive with the way you look now?

1018
01:22:42,932 --> 01:22:44,980
And I'm being serious, too.

1019
01:22:45,972 --> 01:22:48,942
Fuck you. Press conference over.

1020
01:22:54,132 --> 01:22:55,941
- That was hairy.
- Well, you got noticed, Clive.

1021
01:22:55,972 --> 01:22:57,258
I'll tell you that.

1022
01:22:57,332 --> 01:22:58,936
I thought it went well,
to be honest.

1023
01:22:59,012 --> 01:23:00,776
They don't like it
when it's not going their way.

1024
01:23:00,812 --> 01:23:02,496
- Clive.
- That's the game.

1025
01:23:02,612 --> 01:23:04,853
- See you.
- See you later.

1026
01:23:04,932 --> 01:23:06,821
- James, are you all right?
- Good, yeah.

1027
01:23:06,932 --> 01:23:08,616
Listen, I think
I've got something for you

1028
01:23:08,692 --> 01:23:10,456
on that last question, about Niki.

1029
01:23:10,492 --> 01:23:13,098
- You heard about that?
- I did.

1030
01:23:14,332 --> 01:23:16,061
James.

1031
01:23:22,292 --> 01:23:24,863
Please, James...

1032
01:23:25,852 --> 01:23:28,776
Now go home to your wife
and ask her how you look.

1033
01:23:31,212 --> 01:23:32,623
Prick.

1034
01:23:49,492 --> 01:23:54,373
So Niki Lauda, just 42 days after
his near-fatal accident at Nurburgring,

1035
01:23:54,492 --> 01:23:55,982
will race here today at Monza

1036
01:23:56,052 --> 01:23:59,818
against all medical advice
and no doubt in incredible pain.

1037
01:24:32,532 --> 01:24:34,182
<i>...Niki Lauda!</i>

1038
01:24:42,892 --> 01:24:45,293
<i>Photographers,
please clear the grid.</i>

1039
01:24:45,532 --> 01:24:47,694
Niki, it's time.

1040
01:24:49,212 --> 01:24:50,702
Okay?

1041
01:24:57,372 --> 01:24:58,783
<i>Please clear the grid.</i>

1042
01:25:01,412 --> 01:25:03,540
<i>One minute to go.</i>

1043
01:25:49,332 --> 01:25:52,176
<i>The returning Niki Lauda
seems overwhelmed.</i>

1044
01:25:52,252 --> 01:25:54,698
<i>He's being overtaken by car after car.</i>

1045
01:26:04,492 --> 01:26:07,621
<i>Lauda's off line.
He runs wide onto the grass.</i>

1046
01:26:12,452 --> 01:26:14,136
<i>He wrestles it back onto the track,</i>

1047
01:26:14,332 --> 01:26:17,142
<i>but that was a bad moment for Niki.</i>

1048
01:26:21,012 --> 01:26:23,219
<i>Niki Lauda's the reigning
world champion,</i>

1049
01:26:23,292 --> 01:26:26,501
<i>but maybe in his current state
he's a danger out there,</i>

1050
01:26:26,652 --> 01:26:29,462
<i>to himself and to the rest of the field.</i>

1051
01:26:31,452 --> 01:26:35,343
<i>And Stuck has collided
with Mario Andretti's Lotus!</i>

1052
01:26:35,492 --> 01:26:38,655
<i>Niki's boxed in. He's got nowhere to go.</i>

1053
01:26:53,092 --> 01:26:56,653
<i>Niki Lauda is actually
making a move. He's on Brambilla's tail.</i>

1054
01:26:59,932 --> 01:27:02,583
<i>He pulls out of the slipstream
to overtake.</i>

1055
01:27:03,332 --> 01:27:05,653
<i>Lauda's starting to find the form</i>

1056
01:27:05,772 --> 01:27:07,740
<i>that, early in this race,
we believed he'd lost.</i>

1057
01:27:14,172 --> 01:27:18,257
Lauda's now lapping faster than
Reutemann and closing the gap ahead.

1058
01:27:22,172 --> 01:27:24,743
<i>Lauda closing on Carlos Reutemann,</i>

1059
01:27:24,852 --> 01:27:28,015
<i>the man called in to be his replacement
in the Ferrari team.</i>

1060
01:27:37,052 --> 01:27:38,861
<i>And there's James Hunt's McLaren,</i>

1061
01:27:38,972 --> 01:27:41,418
<i>smoking stationary
by the side of the road.</i>

1062
01:27:45,052 --> 01:27:48,135
<i>This is bad news for Hunt's
championship hopes.</i>

1063
01:27:52,532 --> 01:27:53,943
<i>It's Ronnie Peterson</i>

1064
01:27:54,052 --> 01:27:56,419
<i>who comes home the winner here at Monza.</i>

1065
01:27:56,612 --> 01:27:59,502
<i>But all eyes are on the man
who finishes a brilliant fourth,</i>

1066
01:28:00,452 --> 01:28:02,580
<i>- Niki Lauda!</i>

1067
01:28:43,452 --> 01:28:45,773
<i>What a race, what a man,
what a season.</i>

1068
01:28:45,852 --> 01:28:48,014
With a fourth-place finish
and three priceless points,

1069
01:28:48,092 --> 01:28:50,094
it means that Niki Lauda
is a major step closer

1070
01:28:50,132 --> 01:28:52,339
to retaining the World Championship.

1071
01:29:51,492 --> 01:29:55,019
<i>So, the long, gruelling
and incredibly dramatic season</i>

1072
01:29:55,052 --> 01:29:57,419
<i>comes down to this final race in Japan</i>

1073
01:29:57,492 --> 01:30:00,018
<i>in the shadow of Mount Fuji.</i>

1074
01:30:00,092 --> 01:30:01,537
<i>Niki Lauda goes into</i>

1075
01:30:01,572 --> 01:30:03,017
<i>this deciding race at Fuji</i>

1076
01:30:03,092 --> 01:30:05,254
<i>just three points ahead of James Hunt.</i>

1077
01:30:05,332 --> 01:30:09,621
<i>Hunt knowing he must beat the Austrian
fair and square to take the title.</i>

1078
01:30:11,172 --> 01:30:14,699
James, do you think
you can cope with the pressure?

1079
01:30:14,732 --> 01:30:18,259
Well, I've never really understood
what that means. I love my job.

1080
01:30:18,372 --> 01:30:20,420
I love competing. I love racing.

1081
01:30:20,612 --> 01:30:22,455
<i>Maybe you should ask Niki.</i>

1082
01:30:22,532 --> 01:30:24,853
He's the World Champion.
He's got everything to lose.

1083
01:30:24,892 --> 01:30:27,213
<i>Mr Lauda,
are you feeling pressure?</i>

1084
01:30:27,292 --> 01:30:29,738
Do I look like I'm feeling pressure?

1085
01:30:31,812 --> 01:30:35,942
I am World Champion, and on the verge
to become World Champion again.

1086
01:30:36,052 --> 01:30:38,054
Hunt now has the opportunity to win,

1087
01:30:38,132 --> 01:30:40,214
but it's not so easy
to become a champion.

1088
01:30:40,292 --> 01:30:43,421
You have to really believe it
to make it possible.

1089
01:30:43,572 --> 01:30:45,620
James, is there anything
you'd like to add?

1090
01:30:45,732 --> 01:30:49,657
If Niki is being tricky and getting
a kicky out of playing mind games...

1091
01:30:49,732 --> 01:30:52,099
...then fine, I'm flattered.

1092
01:30:52,212 --> 01:30:55,773
But the fact is, momentum is with me.
I've never felt better.

1093
01:30:55,892 --> 01:30:58,463
And I fully expect the next
press conference we will have

1094
01:30:58,572 --> 01:31:00,734
will be with me as World Champion.

1095
01:31:02,572 --> 01:31:05,018
How will you cope
with the weather, bad conditions?

1096
01:31:05,092 --> 01:31:08,574
Intermittent heavy rain
has been forecast here at Fuji today,

1097
01:31:08,652 --> 01:31:12,134
along with strong winds
and occasional fog

1098
01:31:12,252 --> 01:31:14,141
rolling in from the mountain.

1099
01:31:15,932 --> 01:31:18,583
<i>And so, with today's
Japanese Grand Prix to come,</i>

1100
01:31:18,652 --> 01:31:20,416
<i>Lauda's lead a mere three points.</i>

1101
01:31:20,492 --> 01:31:22,176
<i>What a way to finish the season.</i>

1102
01:31:22,772 --> 01:31:24,262
<i>Hunt or Lauda?</i>

1103
01:31:24,332 --> 01:31:27,336
<i>Well, the final chapter will unfold when
we bring you extended coverage...</i>

1104
01:31:27,452 --> 01:31:30,501
They've got to cancel the race.
It's lethal out there.

1105
01:31:30,572 --> 01:31:32,700
The race is going ahead.

1106
01:31:32,772 --> 01:31:34,615
Television rights have been sold
all around the world.

1107
01:31:34,692 --> 01:31:37,343
The showdown between you and Niki
is all anyone wants to see.

1108
01:31:37,412 --> 01:31:40,814
With heavy rain
continuing to fall here at Fuji,

1109
01:31:40,892 --> 01:31:42,974
a decision has finally been made.

1110
01:31:43,092 --> 01:31:47,017
The 1976 Japanese Grand Prix
will go ahead.

1111
01:31:47,092 --> 01:31:49,777
<i>AH drivers
to your cars, please.</i>

1112
01:32:14,412 --> 01:32:15,823
<i>Five minutes to go.</i>

1113
01:32:59,012 --> 01:33:00,457
- All right?
- All right.

1114
01:33:00,532 --> 01:33:02,853
- Hold still.
- What the hell are you doing?

1115
01:33:02,932 --> 01:33:04,661
To let the condensation out.

1116
01:33:04,732 --> 01:33:07,463
- It'll also let the water in.
- Not if you're leading.

1117
01:33:07,532 --> 01:33:09,899
Trust me,
this race is all about the start.

1118
01:33:11,812 --> 01:33:14,383
- Need a hand here?
- Yeah, hold it, Teddy.

1119
01:33:28,852 --> 01:33:30,502
Okay, start the bastard.

1120
01:33:33,492 --> 01:33:35,142
Good luck, kid.

1121
01:33:36,532 --> 01:33:37,943
Good luck, James.

1122
01:34:17,492 --> 01:34:19,494
<i>Thirty seconds to go.</i>

1123
01:34:38,932 --> 01:34:41,094
<i>Electric tension here at Fuji.</i>

1124
01:34:41,172 --> 01:34:46,212
<i>80,000 bedraggled race fans and
the racing grudge match of the decade.</i>

1125
01:34:46,292 --> 01:34:48,420
<i>And there's Mario Andretti
in pole position,</i>

1126
01:34:48,492 --> 01:34:50,494
<i>James Hunt alongside him.</i>

1127
01:34:52,652 --> 01:34:54,575
<i>On Row 2 of the grid,</i>

1128
01:34:54,652 --> 01:34:56,541
<i>there is Niki Lauda,</i>

1129
01:34:56,612 --> 01:34:59,058
<i>and on Row 3 of the grid,
Jody Scheckter from South Africa</i>

1130
01:34:59,132 --> 01:35:00,577
<i>in the six-wheel Tyrrell.</i>

1131
01:35:00,652 --> 01:35:02,734
<i>Behind him,
the rest of the 25-car field.</i>

1132
01:35:20,572 --> 01:35:24,577
There's the flag, and finally
the Japanese Grand Prix is underway!

1133
01:35:36,812 --> 01:35:39,975
<i>In these conditions,
it must be almost impossible to drive</i>

1134
01:35:40,052 --> 01:35:42,054
<i>a 450-horsepower car.</i>

1135
01:36:09,212 --> 01:36:12,216
<i>And it's Andretti who has the lead,
but Hunt is attacking.</i>

1136
01:36:12,292 --> 01:36:15,262
<i>Hunt's going round
the outside of Andretti.</i>

1137
01:36:15,332 --> 01:36:16,902
<i>Niki Lauda following him through.</i>

1138
01:36:16,972 --> 01:36:19,737
<i>Hunt leads into the first right-hander.</i>

1139
01:37:02,812 --> 01:37:04,572
<i>Hunt comes through
to complete his first lap,</i>

1140
01:37:04,612 --> 01:37:06,023
<i>leading the field.</i>

1141
01:37:06,092 --> 01:37:08,220
<i>At least he has clear vision
in front of him.</i>

1142
01:37:08,332 --> 01:37:10,494
<i>Niki Lauda, behind him,
eating his spray.</i>

1143
01:37:29,972 --> 01:37:31,383
<i>Lauda is slowing.</i>

1144
01:37:31,452 --> 01:37:34,342
<i>Niki Lauda is bringing
the Ferrari number one into the pit.</i>

1145
01:37:36,092 --> 01:37:39,301
<i>Some sort of problem, we can't
imagine what, so early in the race.</i>

1146
01:37:45,612 --> 01:37:49,059
What's wrong with the car?
What's wrong with the car?

1147
01:37:50,212 --> 01:37:51,941
Niki, what's wrong with the car?

1148
01:37:52,292 --> 01:37:54,374
Nothing. Car's perfect.

1149
01:37:58,772 --> 01:38:01,139
- What are you doing?
- I'm stopping.

1150
01:38:01,212 --> 01:38:03,374
<i>His mechanics
are asking what the problem is.</i>

1151
01:38:03,452 --> 01:38:05,773
<i>But wait!
Niki Lauda's getting out of the car!</i>

1152
01:38:05,892 --> 01:38:07,496
This is sensational!

1153
01:38:07,572 --> 01:38:10,496
The reigning World Champion,
Niki Lauda, is out of this race.

1154
01:38:11,412 --> 01:38:13,096
It's too dangerous.

1155
01:38:13,172 --> 01:38:16,381
Niki, you want me to say there was
a problem with the car, for the media?

1156
01:38:17,692 --> 01:38:19,182
No.

1157
01:38:19,572 --> 01:38:20,983
Tell them the truth.

1158
01:38:21,852 --> 01:38:23,422
<i>Now, what is happening?</i>

1159
01:38:23,532 --> 01:38:27,457
<i>They're talking to the team manager.
Lauda explaining something.</i>

1160
01:38:43,012 --> 01:38:46,300
<i>With Lauda out, James Hunt
knows he has to finish this race</i>

1161
01:38:46,372 --> 01:38:50,138
<i>in third place or higher
to be World Champion.</i>

1162
01:38:50,212 --> 01:38:52,897
<i>But the job's not done yet
for James Hunt.</i>

1163
01:38:52,972 --> 01:38:57,580
<i>In these dreadful conditions,
he still has to go the distance.</i>

1164
01:38:58,692 --> 01:39:00,535
<i>Fifteen laps to go here at Fuji.</i>

1165
01:39:00,652 --> 01:39:02,734
<i>James Hunt or Niki Lauda?</i>

1166
01:39:02,812 --> 01:39:05,895
<i>This extraordinary season
is not over yet.</i>

1167
01:39:05,972 --> 01:39:09,419
<i>In this treacherous final round,
can James Hunt hang on?</i>

1168
01:39:09,932 --> 01:39:11,775
<i>And the scoreboard tells a story.</i>

1169
01:39:11,852 --> 01:39:14,662
<i>Lap 58. Hunt in the lead.</i>

1170
01:39:16,652 --> 01:39:18,495
Oh, God, his tyres, they're blistering.

1171
01:39:20,132 --> 01:39:21,896
<i>Brambilla very close behind now,</i>

1172
01:39:21,972 --> 01:39:23,940
<i>closing on him all the time now.</i>

1173
01:39:24,052 --> 01:39:27,215
<i>And he's trying to drive
inside James Hunt.</i>

1174
01:39:27,292 --> 01:39:29,818
<i>Hunt cuts across the orange March nose.</i>

1175
01:39:29,932 --> 01:39:32,219
<i>Hunt's not having that at all.
And he's spinning.</i>

1176
01:39:32,292 --> 01:39:35,455
<i>He missed Hunt there, but almost
took James Hunt out of the race</i>

1177
01:39:35,532 --> 01:39:37,899
<i>and out of the world championship.</i>

1178
01:39:37,972 --> 01:39:40,703
<i>Now we find Mario Andretti
closing on James Hunt.</i>

1179
01:39:45,252 --> 01:39:47,220
<i>Mario Andretti's going past Hunt!</i>

1180
01:39:47,692 --> 01:39:50,696
<i>Hunt is slowing. James Hunt
seems to have a problem.</i>

1181
01:39:56,532 --> 01:39:58,296
<i>Despite these wet conditions,</i>

1182
01:39:58,372 --> 01:40:00,101
<i>these wet-weather tyres
do wear extremely fast.</i>

1183
01:40:00,212 --> 01:40:02,340
Hunt's tyres, they've gone.

1184
01:40:02,572 --> 01:40:06,258
<i>Hunt nursing his car
back to the pit stop.</i>

1185
01:40:08,252 --> 01:40:10,300
<i>That back marker's going past Hunt.</i>

1186
01:40:22,732 --> 01:40:25,417
<i>Look at that left front tyre...
Right front tyre, sorry.</i>

1187
01:40:25,492 --> 01:40:28,655
<i>No tread on it at all.
And the other one is flat.</i>

1188
01:40:28,812 --> 01:40:30,940
Let's go! Let's go!

1189
01:40:35,492 --> 01:40:37,893
Okay? When did you break
your gear lever?

1190
01:40:37,972 --> 01:40:39,576
Nine or ten laps ago.

1191
01:40:39,652 --> 01:40:42,098
- Alastair, we need to lift it.
- Come on!

1192
01:40:42,212 --> 01:40:43,896
<i>- At the front.
-  Let's go.</i>

1193
01:40:43,972 --> 01:40:47,181
<i>Regazzoni's Ferrari
and Jacques Lafitte in the Ligier</i>

1194
01:40:47,252 --> 01:40:48,902
have gone ahead.

1195
01:40:49,012 --> 01:40:50,616
Come on, hurry!

1196
01:40:50,692 --> 01:40:53,741
You did it.
You're going to be World Champion!

1197
01:40:53,812 --> 01:40:55,257
Not yet.

1198
01:40:55,332 --> 01:40:59,098
<i>A few laps ago, James Hunt
was looking like champion elect.</i>

1199
01:40:59,172 --> 01:41:01,539
<i>Now it looks as though
it's all gone wrong for him.</i>

1200
01:41:02,972 --> 01:41:04,383
- James.
- Come on!

1201
01:41:04,452 --> 01:41:05,897
- Listen.
- What?

1202
01:41:05,972 --> 01:41:08,213
Just go easy out there.

1203
01:41:08,292 --> 01:41:12,263
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying look after yourself.

1204
01:41:12,332 --> 01:41:14,221
We want you back in one piece.

1205
01:41:14,292 --> 01:41:17,660
You're too far back. There's
too many drivers in front of you.

1206
01:41:17,732 --> 01:41:21,737
- There's always next year.
- So that's it? It's over?

1207
01:41:22,132 --> 01:41:23,622
Clear!

1208
01:41:23,692 --> 01:41:25,217
<i>James.</i>

1209
01:41:26,892 --> 01:41:28,815
- Clear!
- Fuck it!

1210
01:41:32,732 --> 01:41:35,975
James Hunt rejoins the race
in sixth position.

1211
01:41:36,052 --> 01:41:39,943
<i>There are four laps left to go.
Surely no way back for the Brit now.</i>

1212
01:41:59,812 --> 01:42:01,052
Concentrate, Superstar.

1213
01:42:01,252 --> 01:42:02,936
<i>Just brings it back under control.</i>

1214
01:42:03,052 --> 01:42:04,258
<i>Sliding the McLaren</i>

1215
01:42:04,332 --> 01:42:05,572
<i>on the very edge there.</i>

1216
01:42:07,492 --> 01:42:08,778
<i>Hunt's M23</i>

1217
01:42:08,892 --> 01:42:10,532
<i>twitching this way and that
under braking.</i>

1218
01:42:10,572 --> 01:42:11,972
And he almost loses it right there.

1219
01:42:12,092 --> 01:42:14,813
<i>Hunt on the tail
of Jacques Lafitte in the blue Ligier.</i>

1220
01:42:22,772 --> 01:42:24,183
Oh, don't do it, James.

1221
01:42:27,612 --> 01:42:29,182
<i>He's inches away
from the pit wall.</i>

1222
01:42:29,252 --> 01:42:31,061
<i>He's inches away from the Ligier.</i>

1223
01:42:40,092 --> 01:42:42,493
<i>James Hunt has made up another place,</i>

1224
01:42:42,572 --> 01:42:43,573
<i>but it's not enough,</i>

1225
01:42:43,652 --> 01:42:44,892
<i>and this race is running out.</i>

1226
01:42:53,932 --> 01:42:55,934
<i>And Watson has spun.
Watson has spun.</i>

1227
01:43:00,572 --> 01:43:03,337
<i>Hunt manages to weave his way
between that back marker</i>

1228
01:43:03,412 --> 01:43:05,414
<i>and the stationary Penske.</i>

1229
01:43:05,492 --> 01:43:07,494
He's catching Regazzoni

1230
01:43:07,572 --> 01:43:09,222
but, in these conditions,
it's one thing to catch up,

1231
01:43:09,292 --> 01:43:11,499
it's quite another to overtake.

1232
01:43:14,892 --> 01:43:19,022
<i>He's alongside Clay Regazzoni.
This could be the world championship.</i>

1233
01:43:27,452 --> 01:43:28,977
<i>He's got him!</i>

1234
01:43:44,252 --> 01:43:46,334
<i>Hunt crosses the line.</i>

1235
01:43:46,412 --> 01:43:50,019
<i>Now, he needed to finish third to score
enough points to be World Champion,</i>

1236
01:43:50,092 --> 01:43:54,620
<i>and in the confusion here, we're being
told that he may have finished fifth.</i>

1237
01:43:54,692 --> 01:43:56,820
He finished fifth?

1238
01:43:56,892 --> 01:43:59,702
<i>Our lap charts
show Hunt in third place.</i>

1239
01:43:59,772 --> 01:44:01,695
<i>Well, if the scoreboard's right,</i>

1240
01:44:01,772 --> 01:44:04,298
<i>it means he's just missed out
on the championship.</i>

1241
01:44:04,372 --> 01:44:08,013
<i>Crushing defeat for Hunt
after such a heroic drive.</i>

1242
01:44:11,972 --> 01:44:14,498
I can see the race stewards conferring,

1243
01:44:14,572 --> 01:44:16,222
examining the official lap charts.

1244
01:44:16,292 --> 01:44:18,693
<i>We're just going to have to wait
for their verdict here.</i>

1245
01:44:36,332 --> 01:44:37,902
Let's get you out of there, buddy.

1246
01:44:37,972 --> 01:44:40,054
I'm sorry, Teddy. I'm sorry.
I thought I could make up the ground.

1247
01:44:40,132 --> 01:44:42,214
Sorry? What are you talking about?
You did it.

1248
01:44:42,292 --> 01:44:45,057
- Did what?
- Jesus. You crazy bastard.

1249
01:44:45,132 --> 01:44:48,341
You came third. You got the points.
You're champion of the world!

1250
01:44:48,852 --> 01:44:52,095
<i>James Hunt
is now officially confirmed</i>

1251
01:44:52,212 --> 01:44:54,260
<i>as finishing third here in Japan,</i>

1252
01:44:54,892 --> 01:44:58,533
<i>and that means
he is champion of the world.</i>

1253
01:45:00,012 --> 01:45:05,303
<i>Our new World Champion,
James Hunt, by just one single point.</i>

1254
01:45:10,492 --> 01:45:11,982
<i>Did we really win?</i>

1255
01:45:16,052 --> 01:45:18,293
World bloody Champion!

1256
01:45:27,092 --> 01:45:28,981
Tell us, James,
what are you going to do now?

1257
01:45:29,052 --> 01:45:31,214
I shall be getting drunk.

1258
01:45:31,732 --> 01:45:34,463
It's wonderful,
an absolute dream...

1259
01:46:21,452 --> 01:46:23,454
<i>And our special guest,</i>

1260
01:46:23,532 --> 01:46:25,375
<i>Formula 1 champion James Hunt.</i>

1261
01:46:48,772 --> 01:46:50,854
Wait. Come on.

1262
01:46:54,012 --> 01:46:55,502
<i>There's no better motor oil</i>

1263
01:46:55,572 --> 01:46:57,176
<i>than Havoline.</i>

1264
01:47:07,692 --> 01:47:09,615
Yes, me, too.
Where are we going?

1265
01:47:09,692 --> 01:47:11,182
Anywhere I want to go.

1266
01:47:11,252 --> 01:47:13,533
And I don't have to hijack it, either.

1267
01:47:13,572 --> 01:47:15,222
As long as I pay for it.

1268
01:47:15,292 --> 01:47:17,613
I'm starving.
Let's get some food.

1269
01:47:28,732 --> 01:47:30,461
- Where are we going?
- You lot go ahead.

1270
01:47:30,532 --> 01:47:32,500
I won't be a minute.

1271
01:47:38,412 --> 01:47:40,016
Good to see you.

1272
01:47:44,092 --> 01:47:46,493
I heard you were spending
more and more time in one of these.

1273
01:47:46,892 --> 01:47:48,860
- Do you fly?
- No.

1274
01:47:49,252 --> 01:47:50,742
I don't think they'd insure me.

1275
01:47:50,892 --> 01:47:52,735
You should try.
It's good for discipline.

1276
01:47:52,932 --> 01:47:55,412
You have to stay within the rules,
stick to regulations,

1277
01:47:55,532 --> 01:47:58,103
suppress the ego.
It helps with the racing.

1278
01:47:58,212 --> 01:48:01,182
And there I was thinking
you were about to wax lyrical

1279
01:48:01,252 --> 01:48:02,856
about the romance of flight.

1280
01:48:03,212 --> 01:48:04,782
No, that's all bullshit.

1281
01:48:05,932 --> 01:48:07,377
So, what brings you here?

1282
01:48:08,532 --> 01:48:11,012
A friend's wedding.
At least I think it was a wedding.

1283
01:48:11,092 --> 01:48:13,936
Might have been a birthday or something.
It's all a bit of a blur.

1284
01:48:14,012 --> 01:48:15,298
How about you? Have you been at Fiorano?

1285
01:48:15,332 --> 01:48:16,493
Pre-season testing.

1286
01:48:16,612 --> 01:48:18,535
- You're relentless.
- Thank you.

1287
01:48:18,612 --> 01:48:20,774
I'm not sure that was meant
as a compliment.

1288
01:48:20,852 --> 01:48:23,139
When do you start testing? Next week?

1289
01:48:23,172 --> 01:48:25,140
No. What, are you nuts?

1290
01:48:25,212 --> 01:48:26,941
I didn't just win
the biggest thing of my life

1291
01:48:27,012 --> 01:48:28,457
so I could get right back to work.

1292
01:48:29,772 --> 01:48:32,457
Why? You have to.

1293
01:48:32,772 --> 01:48:36,140
To prove to all the people who will
always say you just won it because...

1294
01:48:36,212 --> 01:48:39,614
Because of what?
Because of your accident?

1295
01:48:41,132 --> 01:48:43,180
Niki, is that other people,
or is that you?

1296
01:48:43,812 --> 01:48:46,895
I won, okay? On the all-important day,
when it came down to it,

1297
01:48:46,972 --> 01:48:49,816
we raced on equal terms,
equally good cars.

1298
01:48:49,892 --> 01:48:52,054
And I put my life on the line,
and I saw it through.

1299
01:48:52,132 --> 01:48:54,180
- And you call that winning?
- Yes.

1300
01:48:54,292 --> 01:48:56,374
The risks were totally unacceptable.

1301
01:48:56,892 --> 01:48:59,372
You were prepared to die.
To me, that's losing.

1302
01:48:59,492 --> 01:49:01,062
Yes, I was. I admit it.

1303
01:49:01,132 --> 01:49:03,976
I was prepared to die
to beat you that day.

1304
01:49:04,012 --> 01:49:06,982
And that's the effect you have on me.
You'd pushed me that far.

1305
01:49:07,092 --> 01:49:08,503
And it felt great.

1306
01:49:09,412 --> 01:49:11,733
I mean, hell,
isn't that what we're in this for?

1307
01:49:11,812 --> 01:49:15,180
To stare death in the face
and to cheat it?

1308
01:49:15,532 --> 01:49:19,332
Come on, there's nobility in that.
It's... It's like being knights.

1309
01:49:20,332 --> 01:49:22,096
You English, you're such assholes.

1310
01:49:23,052 --> 01:49:24,497
You know my position.

1311
01:49:24,772 --> 01:49:26,183
Twenty per cent risk.

1312
01:49:26,252 --> 01:49:30,018
No, no, no, Niki, don't bring the
percentages into this. Don't be a pro.

1313
01:49:30,052 --> 01:49:32,703
The minute you do that,
you kill what's good about this.

1314
01:49:33,012 --> 01:49:34,776
You kill the sport.

1315
01:49:37,892 --> 01:49:39,542
James!

1316
01:49:39,852 --> 01:49:41,695
- James!
- Come on!

1317
01:49:44,692 --> 01:49:46,057
I've got to go.

1318
01:49:47,572 --> 01:49:49,540
Careful in this thing.

1319
01:49:50,572 --> 01:49:52,062
James.

1320
01:49:57,292 --> 01:50:01,058
You know, in hospital, the toughest part
of my treatment was the vacuum.

1321
01:50:01,372 --> 01:50:04,296
Pumping the shit out of my lungs.
It was hell.

1322
01:50:05,372 --> 01:50:07,295
And while doing it,
I was watching television.

1323
01:50:07,892 --> 01:50:10,657
- You winning all my points.
- Your points?

1324
01:50:10,732 --> 01:50:12,939
"That bastard Hunt," I would say.
"I hate that guy."

1325
01:50:13,492 --> 01:50:15,574
And then one day
the doctor came and said,

1326
01:50:15,652 --> 01:50:17,939
"Mr Lauda,
may I offer a piece of advice?

1327
01:50:18,052 --> 01:50:21,738
"Stop thinking of it as a curse to
have been given an enemy in life.

1328
01:50:21,812 --> 01:50:23,974
"It can be a blessing, too.

1329
01:50:24,052 --> 01:50:26,817
"A wise man gets more from his enemies
than a fool from his friends."

1330
01:50:27,452 --> 01:50:29,739
And you know what? He was right.

1331
01:50:32,332 --> 01:50:36,098
Look at us. We were both
a pair of kids when we met.

1332
01:50:36,132 --> 01:50:37,941
Hot-headed jerks in Formula 3.

1333
01:50:37,972 --> 01:50:39,815
Disowned by our families.

1334
01:50:39,932 --> 01:50:41,297
Headed nowhere.

1335
01:50:42,412 --> 01:50:44,699
And now we're both
champions of the world.

1336
01:50:44,772 --> 01:50:46,183
It was not bad, huh?

1337
01:50:47,252 --> 01:50:49,175
No, it's not bad.

1338
01:50:49,252 --> 01:50:52,813
So, don't let me down now.
I need you busting my balls.

1339
01:50:53,252 --> 01:50:56,017
- Get back to work.
- I will, Niki, I will.

1340
01:50:56,772 --> 01:50:58,820
But I intend to enjoy myself first.

1341
01:50:59,172 --> 01:51:01,493
Some of life needs to be for pleasure.

1342
01:51:01,612 --> 01:51:04,934
What's the point of having
a million cups and medals and planes

1343
01:51:05,012 --> 01:51:07,174
if you don't have any fun?

1344
01:51:07,972 --> 01:51:09,701
How is that winning?

1345
01:51:10,772 --> 01:51:13,503
- James!
- We're gonna leave without you!

1346
01:51:14,012 --> 01:51:15,457
James!

1347
01:51:19,292 --> 01:51:20,703
I'll see you on race day, champ.

1348
01:51:22,452 --> 01:51:24,614
You will... champ.

1349
01:51:27,132 --> 01:51:28,896
You look good, Niki.

1350
01:51:29,452 --> 01:51:32,342
The only guy to have his face burnt off
and it be an improvement.

1351
01:51:39,172 --> 01:51:41,220
<i>Of course,
he didn't listen to me.</i>

1352
01:51:41,292 --> 01:51:42,737
<i>For James,</i>

1353
01:51:42,812 --> 01:51:44,974
<i>one world title was enough.</i>

1354
01:51:45,012 --> 01:51:46,502
<i>He had proved</i>

1355
01:51:46,532 --> 01:51:49,820
<i>what he needed to prove, to himself</i>

1356
01:51:49,892 --> 01:51:52,179
<i>and anyone who doubted him.</i>

1357
01:51:53,012 --> 01:51:54,901
<i>And two years later he retired.</i>

1358
01:51:55,172 --> 01:51:58,813
<i>When I saw him next in London
seven years later,</i>

1359
01:51:58,932 --> 01:52:01,060
<i>me as champion again,</i>

1360
01:52:01,172 --> 01:52:03,061
<i>him as broadcaster,</i>

1361
01:52:03,132 --> 01:52:07,535
<i>he was barefoot
on a bicycle with a flat tyre.</i>

1362
01:52:07,652 --> 01:52:10,496
<i>Still living each day like his last.</i>

1363
01:52:12,252 --> 01:52:13,742
<i>When I heard he'd died,</i>

1364
01:52:13,852 --> 01:52:16,219
<i>aged 45, of a heart attack,</i>

1365
01:52:16,332 --> 01:52:17,857
<i>I wasn't surprised.</i>

1366
01:52:18,852 --> 01:52:20,741
<i>I was just sad.</i>

1367
01:52:22,092 --> 01:52:23,935
<i>People always think of us as rivals,</i>

1368
01:52:24,012 --> 01:52:27,619
<i>but he was among the very few I liked,</i>

1369
01:52:28,932 --> 01:52:31,902
<i>and even fewer that I respected.</i>

1370
01:52:35,052 --> 01:52:37,783
<i>He remains the only person I envied.</i>

